1176
01:57:46,680 --> 01:57:49,478
a whole new world opens up.

1177
01:57:52,480 --> 01:57:56,109
You got that kind of cold,
empty feeling inside of you?

1178
01:57:56,200 --> 01:58:00,239
- Yes. Do all gold miners get that?
- It's very common.

1179
01:58:00,320 --> 01:58:02,276
What do they do for it?

1180
01:58:03,360 --> 01:58:05,555
I'll show you.

1181
01:58:10,760 --> 01:58:12,910
Are we going in a saloon?

1182
01:58:13,000 --> 01:58:15,912
That's where
the medicine closet is.

1183
01:58:16,000 --> 01:58:19,390
It's part of that whole new world
I was telling you about.

1184
01:58:20,560 --> 01:58:22,312
After you, Columbus.

1185
01:58:23,960 --> 01:58:29,956
Gentle music fills the sky
At No Name City

1186
01:58:30,040 --> 01:58:35,273
And the days, they whisper by
At No Name City

1187
01:58:36,840 --> 01:58:42,870
Sure, there's not a spot as rare in
All heaven or in Erin

1188
01:58:43,840 --> 01:58:50,712
Let me live until I die
In No Name Town

1189
01:59:19,200 --> 01:59:21,555
That's good. My first drink.

1190
01:59:37,880 --> 01:59:42,112
- You feeling all right?
- Yes, sir. Thank you.

1191
01:59:44,920 --> 01:59:48,674
That cold, hollow feeling
is almost gone.

1192
01:59:48,760 --> 01:59:50,876
Bartender, cigars.

1193
01:59:54,880 --> 01:59:56,677
Thank you.

1194
02:00:18,040 --> 02:00:20,998
I'll bet that's the strongest cigar
you ever smoked.

1195
02:00:22,080 --> 02:00:25,595
It's the first cigar I ever smoked.
It's delicious.

1196
02:00:29,360 --> 02:00:32,636
- You all right, Mr Rumson?
- Fine.

1197
02:00:49,080 --> 02:00:52,436
Why do you think my father
is so dead set against saloons?

1198
02:00:52,520 --> 02:00:56,593
Cos farmers ain't got the time
to enjoy the good things in life.

1199
02:00:56,680 --> 02:00:58,716
Farmer's got a busy day...

1200
02:00:58,800 --> 02:01:02,031
Got to pull them turnips,
talk about the weather.

1201
02:01:02,120 --> 02:01:04,953
That's about as much
as he can handle.

1202
02:01:09,400 --> 02:01:11,356
Quiet!

1203
02:01:11,440 --> 02:01:14,591
- Who are they, Mr Rumson?
- They're on the menu.

1204
02:01:17,080 --> 02:01:19,036
I don't understand, sir.

1205
02:01:26,040 --> 02:01:29,999
You ain't gonna tell me that you
ain't never had a woman, neither?

1206
02:01:30,520 --> 02:01:32,476
No, sir, I haven't.

1207
02:01:34,680 --> 02:01:36,432
That's terrible!

1208
02:01:37,520 --> 02:01:41,229
Do you know you could go blind?
We got to do something about that.

1209
02:01:41,320 --> 02:01:43,072
I wouldn't know what to do.

1210
02:01:43,160 --> 02:01:46,869
Don't worry. With your talent,
you'll catch on in no time.

1211
02:01:50,720 --> 02:01:55,157
Willie, if you was to go trapping
for the first time,

1212
02:01:55,240 --> 02:01:58,437
who would you take along as a guide?

1213
02:02:00,680 --> 02:02:04,468
That would be Gracie.
She loves adventure.

1214
02:02:28,000 --> 02:02:31,834
Grace, I give you the boy.

1215
02:02:32,800 --> 02:02:35,109
Give me back the man.

1216
02:02:44,680 --> 02:02:47,558
- That was the best.
- You think so?

1217
02:02:47,640 --> 02:02:51,519
I like smoking and drinking,
but they can't touch the last one.

1218
02:02:51,600 --> 02:02:53,352
That's got everything.

1219
02:02:53,440 --> 02:02:56,750
Most people'd go along
with that. Well, good night.

1220
02:02:56,840 --> 02:03:00,355
Mrs Rumson will be sorry
you're not coming for dinner.

1221
02:03:00,440 --> 02:03:04,228
The last thing she said this morning
was to be sure and bring you.

1222
02:03:04,320 --> 02:03:09,553
- In that case, maybe I will.
- Good. I'll walk you home after.

1223
02:03:13,120 --> 02:03:16,715
Remember, you wasn't in no
tunnels and wasn't in no saloon.

1224
02:03:16,800 --> 02:03:18,870
I remember.

1225
02:03:18,960 --> 02:03:22,350
We thank thee, Lord,
for the two of these friends...

1226
02:03:24,120 --> 02:03:25,712
Shut the door.

1227
02:03:28,880 --> 02:03:32,270
For this
we thank thee, Lord. Amen.

1228
02:03:34,640 --> 02:03:38,076
- Will you wipe your feet off?
- Evening, Ben. Sit down.

1229
02:03:38,160 --> 02:03:39,912
Evening, Elizabeth.

1230
02:03:47,080 --> 02:03:50,834
Well, Pardner,
you handled grace pretty good.

1231
02:03:50,920 --> 02:03:54,913
Not as good as Horton did this
afternoon, but pretty good.

1232
02:03:57,160 --> 02:03:59,549
- Where have you been?
- Gold mining.

1233
02:03:59,640 --> 02:04:03,599
Your son's the most natural-born
gold miner that I ever met.

1234
02:04:03,680 --> 02:04:06,672
I brought him up not
to be afraid to try anything.

1235
02:04:06,760 --> 02:04:09,399
That boy tries everything.

1236
02:04:09,480 --> 02:04:14,508
Did you know that the Fentys had
an apple farm back in Pennsylvania?

1237
02:04:14,600 --> 02:04:16,192
Applejack?

1238
02:04:16,280 --> 02:04:20,671
- No, we did not make applejack.
- Then why grow apples?

1239
02:04:20,760 --> 02:04:26,039
Mr Rumson, should everything
from the earth be used for liquor?

1240
02:04:26,120 --> 02:04:29,874
- Whenever possible.
- You should read the Bible.

1241
02:04:29,960 --> 02:04:31,996
I have read the Bible.

1242
02:04:32,080 --> 02:04:34,310
Didn't that discourage you
from drinking?

1243
02:04:34,400 --> 02:04:36,595
No. Killed my appetite for reading.

1244
02:04:38,160 --> 02:04:41,630
We've been telling the Fentys
what good land's all around here.

1245
02:04:41,720 --> 02:04:45,713
- We're thinking of settling here.
- Great!

1246
02:04:45,800 --> 02:04:50,112
That news is so God damn great,
I need a drink.

1247
02:04:50,200 --> 02:04:52,873
Don't listen to him.
He's always joking.

1248
02:04:53,880 --> 02:04:57,953
- Elizabeth, the whisky's gone.
- I know. I poured it all out.

1249
02:04:58,040 --> 02:05:02,272
- You what?
- Out of courtesy to our guests.

1250
02:05:02,360 --> 02:05:05,875
If you want a drink,
get your carcass out of this house.

1251
02:05:07,400 --> 02:05:10,437
You can't order a man
out of his own house.

1252
02:05:10,520 --> 02:05:13,239
- His house?
- That's right. It's his house.

1253
02:05:13,320 --> 02:05:17,518
- Mrs Rumson is married to him?
- She's married to the both of us.

1254
02:05:17,600 --> 02:05:20,831
- At the same time?
- Well, we're pardners.

1255
02:05:20,920 --> 02:05:24,151
- I have never heard...
- Shut up and sit down!

1256
02:05:24,240 --> 02:05:28,119
- Don't order the guests around.
- Why not? It's his fault.

1257
02:05:28,200 --> 02:05:33,433
Without his respectability, we'd
still be a happily married... triple.

1258
02:05:33,520 --> 02:05:36,876
- There's not one drink of whisky?
- Take mine.

1259
02:05:36,960 --> 02:05:38,791
Thank you. You saved my life.

1260
02:05:38,880 --> 02:05:42,111
Horton, how did that bottle
get into your pocket?

1261
02:05:43,440 --> 02:05:47,433
- How long have you been drinking?
- Since this afternoon.

1262
02:05:47,520 --> 02:05:51,308
You don't approve, but until
you've had a good cigar and whisky,

1263
02:05:51,400 --> 02:05:54,153
you're missing
two of the best things in life.

1264
02:05:54,240 --> 02:05:59,837
- Where'd you take him, Ben?
- Damn you, Ben Rumson.

1265
02:05:59,920 --> 02:06:01,876
What are you gonna
teach this boy next?

1266
02:06:01,960 --> 02:06:07,080
How to cheat at cards or
physical education with some floozy?

1267
02:06:07,160 --> 02:06:09,276
That's the best one.

1268
02:06:10,360 --> 02:06:15,718
- Is that what you did today, Ben?
- That's what he did today.

1269
02:06:15,800 --> 02:06:20,351
He's got a talent for dissipation
that is absolutely unique.

1270
02:06:22,040 --> 02:06:27,478
Out. Get out!
I order you out of this house!

1271
02:06:28,560 --> 02:06:31,438
This is not your house!
This is my house!

1272
02:06:32,520 --> 02:06:34,351
That's right. I give her the house.

1273
02:06:37,760 --> 02:06:39,876
If you cross this threshold again,

1274
02:06:39,960 --> 02:06:42,428
I'll shoot you
like any other marauder.

1275
02:06:43,520 --> 02:06:47,513
- What's she so het up about?
- She's got a right to be.

1276
02:06:47,600 --> 02:06:51,388
You had to take your revenge
on the virtue of this boy,

1277
02:06:51,480 --> 02:06:54,278
show him what an ugly town
this really is.

1278
02:06:54,360 --> 02:06:57,636
If we live here,
then we're ugly, too.

1279
02:06:57,720 --> 02:07:00,792
I could never go back
to what we had before.

1280
02:07:00,880 --> 02:07:04,714
It's over and it's done
and it's finished. Now get out.

1281
02:07:04,800 --> 02:07:10,511
- Wait. If Ben goes, I'd have to go.
- Then you go, too.

1282
02:07:32,520 --> 02:07:35,830
- Evening, ma'am.
- Good evening, ma'am.

1283
02:07:39,480 --> 02:07:43,792
You mutton-headed clunk. You knew
she didn't want them to know.

1284
02:07:43,880 --> 02:07:46,599
Elizabeth's a sick woman.

1285
02:07:46,680 --> 02:07:49,478
You got no respect
for anybody or anything.

1286
02:07:49,560 --> 02:07:54,429
I don't have your kind of respect,
sitting there with your hands folded

1287
02:07:54,520 --> 02:07:58,229
and that pious look on your face
after a hard day's thieving.

1288
02:07:58,320 --> 02:08:01,392
- It ain't thieving.
- Then why are we hiding it?

1289
02:08:01,480 --> 02:08:04,438
Why are we talking about it?
She's all alone.

1290
02:08:04,520 --> 02:08:06,875
- Whose fault is that?
- Yours.

1291
02:08:06,960 --> 02:08:08,712
Hers. She threw us out.

1292
02:08:08,800 --> 02:08:11,837
Don't say anything
against Elizabeth around me.

1293
02:08:11,920 --> 02:08:16,198
I'll say anything I want. She's my
wife, paid for, and don't forget it.

1294
02:08:18,520 --> 02:08:20,954
I never do forget it.

1295
02:08:22,720 --> 02:08:27,555
- I got nothing more to say to you.
- You got nothing I want to hear!

1296
02:08:27,640 --> 02:08:29,995
If I catch you
sneaking back without me,

1297
02:08:30,080 --> 02:08:31,832
they'll never find
all of you to bury!

1298
02:08:33,440 --> 02:08:36,034
Bull and bear fight!
Bull and bear fight!

1299
02:08:36,120 --> 02:08:39,510
See the great bull that cut up
the mountain lion in Sonora

1300
02:08:39,600 --> 02:08:43,070
and emerged triumphant
over 10 large dogs!

1301
02:08:43,160 --> 02:08:45,628
Save your souls, heathen scum!

1302
02:08:45,720 --> 02:08:48,917
Allow this butchery
to take place on Sunday,

1303
02:08:49,000 --> 02:08:50,911
and God will wash his hands of you!

1304
02:08:51,000 --> 02:08:52,797
Thank you, parson. Now go.

1305
02:08:52,880 --> 02:08:55,189
God is gonna cause the earth to open

1306
02:08:55,280 --> 02:09:00,149
and swallow up this nest of evil,
and the Lord ain't fooling.

1307
02:09:01,760 --> 02:09:05,673
I hear strange rumblings
in the earth below.

1308
02:09:08,120 --> 02:09:11,908
They' sell a lot of tickets
to the bull and bear fight on Sunday.

1309
02:09:12,440 --> 02:09:15,034
A lot of gold dust is gonna fall.

1310
02:09:15,120 --> 02:09:18,590
But Jack, we don't have
a tunnel under there!

1311
02:09:22,640 --> 02:09:26,758
You bloody maniac!
Why didn't you build one?!

1312
02:09:27,160 --> 02:09:31,039
We can get under there by Sunday.
There's nothing to it.

1313
02:09:32,960 --> 02:09:34,996
Maybe so.

1314
02:09:37,480 --> 02:09:40,313
But we could sure use a bit of help.

1315
02:09:50,920 --> 02:09:54,196
What about that young farmer?
Where's he?

1316
02:09:54,280 --> 02:09:58,751
Horton Fenty? Little did
I realise it, but when he set foot

1317
02:09:58,840 --> 02:10:03,709
on the second storey of Willie's
Saloon, history was in the making.

1318
02:10:03,800 --> 02:10:06,234
- Is that where he is?
- That's where he always is!

1319
02:10:06,320 --> 02:10:09,630
Puffing cigars, drinking,
and knocking on doors.

1320
02:10:09,720 --> 02:10:13,793
If he don't slow down, them girls
are gonna strike for shorter hours.

1321
02:10:15,480 --> 02:10:18,756
I'll see if I can catch him
between rooms tonight.

1322
02:10:20,120 --> 02:10:23,874
If we could divert his energy,
we could be through by morning.

1323
02:10:28,200 --> 02:10:29,758
Come on, bet.

1324
02:10:30,920 --> 02:10:32,478
I'll bet 50.

1325
02:10:33,760 --> 02:10:37,639
- I'll see that and raise you 50.
- Not for me. I'm out.

1326
02:10:40,440 --> 02:10:43,318
Have you seen
the future father of our country?

1327
02:10:43,400 --> 02:10:46,358
- Yeah. He went home.
- When will he be back?

1328
02:10:46,440 --> 02:10:50,433
- Soon as his folks are asleep.
- Tell him I want to see him.

1329
02:10:50,520 --> 02:10:53,353
Leave your door open
and wait your turn.

1330
02:10:55,200 --> 02:10:56,997
Here.

1331
02:11:06,400 --> 02:11:09,710
Pardon me, sir.
Could you lend me $10?

1332
02:11:10,320 --> 02:11:12,515
Why don't you go home and go to bed?

1333
02:11:12,600 --> 02:11:15,672
I was thinking of doing it
the other way around.

1334
02:11:19,480 --> 02:11:22,950
- Thank you, sir.
- I'll see your 50.

1335
02:11:25,320 --> 02:11:27,629
Red seven wins again!

1336
02:11:44,160 --> 02:11:48,233
Pardon me. Here's your $10 back, sir.

1337
02:11:48,760 --> 02:11:51,797
And 10 more. Red seven.

1338
02:12:08,760 --> 02:12:11,877
You're losing a lot of money,
Pardner. Where do you get it all?

1339
02:12:11,960 --> 02:12:14,076
Thieving.

1340
02:12:22,280 --> 02:12:25,955
I would give the world to see
How I used to be

1341
02:12:26,040 --> 02:12:29,715
When I had no axe to grind
Except for choppin' wood

1342
02:12:32,640 --> 02:12:36,235
Day was day, and night was night
Wrong was never right

1343
02:12:36,320 --> 02:12:39,995
It didn't matter where I went
As much as where I stood

1344
02:12:42,800 --> 02:12:46,759
I had dreams
Average size

1345
02:12:46,840 --> 02:12:51,834
There were stars
In the skies

1346
02:12:51,920 --> 02:12:54,718
Not my eyes

1347
02:12:56,800 --> 02:13:01,828
Then I got gold fever

1348
02:13:02,200 --> 02:13:06,318
No rompin', rollin'
Girl-and-fellow stuff

1349
02:13:06,400 --> 02:13:09,790
Can cure the gold fever

1350
02:13:10,880 --> 02:13:13,872
Nothin' can help you
But the yellow stuff

1351
02:13:16,280 --> 02:13:19,636
What can stop that itchin'

1352
02:13:20,040 --> 02:13:23,669
Ain't around the kitchen

1353
02:13:23,760 --> 02:13:29,710
Gold, gold, hooked am I
Susannah, go ahead and cry

1354
02:13:41,080 --> 02:13:44,311
Once we all did honest work
Farmer, lawyer, clerk

1355
02:13:44,400 --> 02:13:48,359
Married men and single men
And some who ain't too sure

1356
02:13:51,360 --> 02:13:54,636
Now I look at them and see
Duplicates of me

1357
02:13:54,720 --> 02:13:58,793
Cured of what we suffered from
And sufferin' from the cure

1358
02:14:01,440 --> 02:14:05,638
Who can say why we came?

1359
02:14:05,720 --> 02:14:09,838
Where's the hope?
Where's the flame?

1360
02:14:10,920 --> 02:14:14,595
We're the same

1361
02:14:16,160 --> 02:14:21,712
When you've got gold fever

1362
02:14:22,800 --> 02:14:25,712
No rompin', rollin'
Girl-and-fellow stuff

1363
02:14:25,800 --> 02:14:29,270
Can cure the gold fever

1364
02:14:30,280 --> 02:14:33,556
Nothin' can help you
But the yellow stuff

1365
02:14:35,920 --> 02:14:39,435
What can stop that itchin'

1366
02:14:39,520 --> 02:14:43,149
Ain't around the kitchen

1367
02:14:43,240 --> 02:14:49,076
Gold, gold, hooked am I
Susannah, go ahead and cry

1368
02:14:50,680 --> 02:14:53,797
Gold fever

1369
02:14:53,880 --> 02:14:56,997
Gold fever

1370
02:14:58,240 --> 02:15:00,595
Gold fever

1371
02:15:02,120 --> 02:15:04,588
Gold fever

1372
02:15:05,760 --> 02:15:08,638
Gold fever

1373
02:15:09,680 --> 02:15:11,636
Deal.

1374
02:15:37,000 --> 02:15:39,036
By God, we made it.

1375
02:15:46,680 --> 02:15:49,990
Now they can open the box office.

1376
02:16:15,400 --> 02:16:17,595
Here's your day's earnings, Ben.

1377
02:16:19,120 --> 02:16:21,475
And here's yours, Pardner.

1378
02:16:25,160 --> 02:16:29,472
- Tell Ben something for me.
- He's right there.

1379
02:16:30,600 --> 02:16:34,036
Just tell him that I'm moving on
before winter sets in.

1380
02:16:34,120 --> 02:16:35,917
He can get himself another Pardner.

1381
02:16:36,000 --> 02:16:39,754
You bummers can divide up
anything I got coming here.

1382
02:16:40,760 --> 02:16:42,478
Where you heading?

1383
02:16:42,560 --> 02:16:46,997
Red Dog. I hear they're
digging it up in chunks there.

1384
02:16:47,120 --> 02:16:51,272
By goom, they're always digging
it up in chunks somewhere else.

1385
02:16:53,480 --> 02:16:56,517
- Good luck, man.
- Thanks, Jack.

1386
02:17:02,920 --> 02:17:07,357
Tell Ben to look in on Elizabeth.
The Fentys are pulling out.

1387
02:17:08,840 --> 02:17:11,035
She'll be alone.

1388
02:17:24,160 --> 02:17:27,550
You stinkin', rotten heathen scum!

1389
02:17:27,640 --> 02:17:30,996
Silence, Judas! Today is Sunday!

1390
02:17:31,080 --> 02:17:35,198
And you are going to hear the word
of God whether you like it or not!

1391
02:17:35,280 --> 02:17:40,434
- Get out of here!
- And the word of the Lord is doom!

1392
02:17:40,520 --> 02:17:42,272
Set the bull on him.

1393
02:17:42,360 --> 02:17:44,715
- You can't do that.
- Let him out!

1394
02:17:46,440 --> 02:17:49,750
...this town of lust and corruption!

1395
02:17:51,760 --> 02:17:53,637
Get out of here.

1396
02:17:55,200 --> 02:17:57,509
Out, out, out.

1397
02:18:00,080 --> 02:18:03,675
You are not going to fight
that bear on the Sabbath.

1398
02:18:08,160 --> 02:18:12,119
I represent the Lord, and the Lord
says get out of this arena.

1399
02:18:13,760 --> 02:18:18,550
The Lord will open the earth, and you
will sink into the pit! You hear?!

1400
02:18:20,560 --> 02:18:25,156
I said, sink into the pit.
I said, sink into the pit!

1401
02:18:28,560 --> 02:18:33,793
- I'll be God damned.
- Hello, parson. Welcome to hell.

1402
02:19:21,160 --> 02:19:25,472
Though I walk through
the valley of the shadow of death...

1403
02:19:25,560 --> 02:19:28,393
You better run through that valley!

1404
02:19:59,880 --> 02:20:04,078
Will you kindly watch where the
hell you're falling, my good man?!

1405
02:20:11,840 --> 02:20:13,637
Now where are you going?

1406
02:20:13,720 --> 02:20:16,518
